<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Baht to Regain Strength This Week: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The Thai baht tends to regain its
strength this week, as international rating agencies are
reportedly moving to upgrade their credit rating to Thailand, a
senior bank official said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ekaratana Suwannava, head of the Department of Currency Trade
of DBS Thai Danu Bank, said in a report that the Thai currency is
appreciating to around 38.88 to 38.91 against U.S. dollar, up from
over 39 baht a dollar over the past week.
</P>
<P>
The positive trend resulted from moves by international rating
agencies to upgrade their credit rating to the Thai economy, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The upward trend of the Thai baht also resulted from stronger
currencies in the Asian region, namely the Singapore dollar and
the Japanese yen, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
