<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0003 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Senate to Perform Duty Before June 24: Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Election Commission has
expressed its confidence that the full 200-seat Senate will be
ready to perform its duty before the reconvention of the House of
Representatives on June 24.
</P>
<P>
The commission said in an announcement Monday that since they
had received few complaints on frauds and forms of vote buying in
Sunday's third round of senatorial election, it believed that the
complete 200-seat Senate could officially start to perform its
duties before June 24, the scheduled date for reconvention of the
House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
However, the commission said that there might be the fourth
round senatorial poll in some provinces.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's third round senatorial election, whose official
results are expected by June 8, was to fill in the remaining 12
seats of the Senate, as winners of the past two polls were
suspended by the Election Commission due to evidences of their
irregular practices.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
