<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Donors Briefed on Bangladesh Opposition's Stand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's main opposition party,
the Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) Monday informed the donor
countries and agencies of its decision to abstain from the budget
session of the parliament which began Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ambassadors and representatives of 17 donor countries and
agencies held a meeting with a five-member delegation of the BNP
at Hotel Sheraton Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Envoys of the United States, Britain, France, Germany, Japan,
Canada Italy, Australia, the Netherlands, Denmark, Sweden, Norway,
European Union and representatives of the World Bank, the
International Monetary Fund, the Asian Development Bank and the
United Nations Development Program took part in the closed-door
meeting which lasted 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The issues of the BNP's abstention from the budget session,
situation following appointment of new Chief Election Commissioner
(CEC) upazila (county) election, law and order situation in the
country and opposition movement against the government came under
discussion.
</P>
<P>
When the envoys questioned why BNP refused to join the current
session of the parliament, delegates of the BNP said they had
decided not to join it as there is "no congenial atmosphere in the
House."
</P>
<P>
As to the Chief Election Commissioner, the BNP reiterated its
demand for immediate resignation of the newly appointed CEC.
</P>
<P>
This kind of meeting between the main opposition party and the
donors started two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
