<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> King Fahd Holds Israel Responsible for Peace Stalemate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, June 5 (Xinhua ) -- Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz held
Israel responsible for the deadlock of the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the opening of the fourth session of the Saudi
Shura (advisory) Council in the Red Sea port city of Jeddah Monday
afternoon, King Fahd said "Israel is the only responsible party for
the dangers facing our region due to its procrastination and
maneuvers."
</P>
<P>
Israel should bring the peace process back on track and respond
positively to the efforts aimed at establishing a fair, lasting and
comprehensive peace in the region on the bases of the U.N. Security
Council resolutions, Madrid reference, and subsequent accords, the
Saudi News Agency quoted the monarch as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, King Fahd reaffirmed Saudi support to Syria until it
recovers its full rights, on top of which the restoration of the
Israel-occupied Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated the Lebanese people and government on the
liberation of south Lebanon from Israeli occupation. "Such victory
would never be achieved without the efforts of the Lebanese valiant
resistance," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
