<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Set up Modern Price Data Base System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is expected to
establish a modern price data base system early next year to
provide accurate information on evaluation of imports for both
customs officials and importers, a senior official said here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Commissioner for Customs Theo Lyimo told a five-day
workshop on price date base design and World Trade Organization
regulations that the new system will give importers detailed
classification lists on the determined values of cargo.
</P>
<P>
"Various transit ports at borders will computerize their
operations for the establishment of price data base system which
will be updated every three months to keep abreast with the
changing patterns of imports," he said.
</P>
<P>
Imports evaluation by the new system will be more accurate and
transparent than the existing system, he explained.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that no action or decision can be taken by
government agencies without a thorough knowledge and mastery of
the new fundamentals of international business.
</P>
<P>
"Tanzania has been obliged to meet the challenges created by
new economic turbulence in increased investment and human resource
training," he said, adding that "the establishing of a
comprehensive price data base is therefore crucial in securing the
revenue."
</P>
<P>
When asked when the new price data base system will become
fully operational, the customs deputy commissioner said that it
will be in place by January next year if preparations go as
planned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Concerned Over Violence in Solomon Islands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Secretary-General expressed his concern over the
escalation of violence in the Solomon Islands and urges that the
hostages be released immediately and constitutional rule restored,
" spokesman Fred Eckhard said.
</P>
<P>
In the context of an 18-month fighting between the two rival
ethnic groups in the southwest Pacific country, armed rebels of
the Malaita Eagle Force captured Prime Minister Bartholemew Ulufa'
alu early Monday, demanded his resignation, according to reports
from the capital of Honiara.
</P>
<P>
The fighting between the Force on the Malaita Island and the
Isatabu Freedom Movement on the main Guadalcanal Island has
resulted in around 60 deaths.
</P>
<P>
Composed of some 900 islands and isles, the Solomon Islands has
an area of over 29,000 square kilometers and a population of about
500,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
