<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic National
Committee (DNC) of the United States will launch a multimillion
dollar television ad campaign for Democratic Party presidential
candidate Al Gore this weekend, party officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ads will run in 14 or 15 states, mostly in the Midwest,
South and Pacific Northwest. It is part of a campaign that will
cost upward of 25 million dollars between now and the Democratic
National Convention in mid-August.
</P>
<P>
The ads will highlight issues including Social Security,
Medicare, the availability of prescription drugs to seniors, the
environment and spotlight Gore's biography,
</P>
