New York Tuesday, urged states to improve the quality and
affordability of child care.
</P>
<P>
He also proposed tax breaks to help parents pay for day care or
to keep their kids at home.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, former Democratic presidential candidate Bill
Bradley reiterated his support for Al Gore Tuesday and disputed
Republican talk that he has failed to endorse Gore.
</P>
<P>
"I said I give him my full support, and that's what I will do,"
Bradley said.
</P>
<P>
He said he will campaign for Democratic candidates,including
Gore, in the fall.  
