<HEADLINE> Russia's Foreign Trade Posts Record Growth in January-April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia's foreign trade volume in the
first four months of this year hit a record high of 40.6 billion U.
S.dollars, up 31.9 percent over the same period of 1999, the
Russian State Customs Committee announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The exports in the period surged 45.3 percent to 30.6 billion
dollars, and the imports increased three percent to 10 billion
dollars, with trade surplus amounting to 20.6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Russia's foreign trade turnover with the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS) countries rose 44.6 percent to eight
billion dollars, of which the exports to Commonwealth nations
soared 46.9 percent to 4.7 billion dollars with the imports up 41.
5 percent to 3.3 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Thus, its favorable trade balance with the CIS states reached 1.
4 billion dollars during January-April, 0.5 billion dollars more
than the corresponding term of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russia's trade volume with the states outside CIS
totaled 32.6 billion dollars, up 29.2 percent. Of them, Russia's
exports to the countries outside CIS jumped 45 percent to 25.9
billion dollars, while its imports from them fell 9.2 percent to 6.
7 billion dollars, said the committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
