<TEXT>

<P>
ATHENS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Greek Economy and Finance Minister
Yiannos Papantoniou said Tuesday that Greece would participate in
the European Union's core for the first time because the country
had won the battle for growth and low inflation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in Athens, just a day after an
EU finance ministers' decision to approve Greece's Economic and
Monetary Union (EMU) membership, Papantoniou said that this was
the last step before a formal approval at an EU summit in Lisbon,
Portugal on June 19.
</P>
<P>
Greece missed the chance to enter into the euro zone last year
when it failed to satisfy the Maastricht criteria on inflation,
deficit and debt, but the country has now met all the five
necessary criteria following intensive convergence efforts.
</P>
<P>
The minister also said that by the summer of 2001, the
majority of the 17 privatizations that were included in the agenda
of the Greek government would be completed.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the Greek government successfully
materialized a program of 15 privatizations,he added. 
