<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 6(Xinhua) -- Egypt on Tuesday proposed to
set up a "Trust Fund For Women or a Globle Facility for Women" to
improve women's status and to promote the equality between men and
women.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was made by Suzanne Mubarak, head of the delegaton
of Egypt to the United Nations General Assembly special session on
women.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the general debate of the special session, Suzanne
Mubarak said this facility would act as an umbrella to existing
institutions, programs and funds charged with the formulation of
strategies.
</P>
<P>
It would also consolidate presently fragmented efforts as well
as increase the resources needed to meet priority areas of
universal concern identified in the Fourth World Conference on
Women in Beijing in 1995, Suzanne Mubarak said.
</P>
<P>
Suzanne Mubarak expressed the hope that the international
donor community together with the U.N. system should match their
partnership rhetoric with concrete actions for better coordination,
better-targeted support and a larger flow of aid resources.
</P>
<P>
Suzanne Mubarak said this special session should agree on
action-oriented recommendations to be submitted to the Millennium
Summit in September so that the gender file could find its
rightful place in the U.N. agenda for the twenty-first century.
</P>
<P>
The special session, under the theme of "Women 2000: Gender
Equality, Development and Peace for the Twenty-first Century,"
opened here Monday and will go through Friday.
</P>
<P>
The special session will consider further actions and
initiatives for achieving gender equality in the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
