<HEADLINE> Cote d'Ivoire Asks France to Cooperate in Arresting Ex-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Cote d'Ivoire has asked France to
cooperate in arresting former President Henry Konan Bedie and some
of his top aides for "embezzlement of public fund," Agence France-
Presse (AFP) report Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The judicial authority of Cote d'Ivoire has issued an
international arrest warrant for Bedie, who is living in exile in
France.
</P>
<P>
The demand has been transmitted to the French embassy in
Abidjan in accordance with a bilateral agreement on judicial
cooperation which was signed in 1961.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutor of the Republic of Cote d'Ivoire Omer Doue has also
issued an international arrest warrant for former Finance Minister
Niamien N'Goran, who is also in exile in France.
</P>
<P>
The military junta of Cote d'Ivoire, led by General Robert Guen,
launched an "operation of clean hands" after coming to power in a
coup on December 24, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Bedie and his entourage were evacuated to France by the French
army on December 26, 1999. 
</P>
