The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- The government filed a revised proposal to break up
Microsoft, rejecting most changes sought by the software company
and putting the case on track for a final ruling within days.
</P>
<P>
-- Secretary of State Albright arrived in the Mideast for talks
with Israeli and Palestinian leaders intended to speed up
negotiations on a permanent peace treaty. Barak said he may
sweeten an offer of West Bank territory, but said Israel must
maintain a settlement presence in the Jordan Valley.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0067 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venus Williams Beaten by Sanchez-Vicario at French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Venus Williams was eliminated in the
quarter-finals at the French Open on Tuesday, losing a baseline
duel against three-time champion Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario, 6-0, 1-6,
6-2.
</P>
<P>
Williams stuck to her groundstrokes against the steadier and
more experienced clay-court expert Sanchez-Vicario.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-seeded Williams was playing in only her third
tournament after being sidelined for six months with tendinitis in
both wrists.
</P>
<P>
Williams started hard, committing 20 errors in the first five
games and lost them all.
</P>
<P>
Even improvement in the second set could not save her, who
looked increasingly tired as she lost a succession of long points
from the baseline.
</P>
<P>
The tournament was her last chance to win a Grand Slam title as
a teen-ager. She turns 20 on June 17, nine days before Wimbledon
begins.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez-Vicario, seeded eighth, won the French Open as a 17-
year-old in 1989, and again in 1994 and 1998. The 28-year-old
will meet fifth-seeded Conchita Martinez or 17-year-old qualifier
Marta Marrero in an all-Spaniard semifinal Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In men's play, unseeded Franco Squillari became the first
Argentine to reach the French Open quarter-finals since 1991,
beating Younes El Aynaoui 6-4, 6-1, 6-3 in a rain-interrupted
match.
</P>
<P>
Squillari, 23, will next play unseeded Albert Costa, who became
the third Spaniard to reach the men's quarter-finals when he won
over No. 9 Lleyton Hewitt, 6-3, 4-6, 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The last Argentine to make in the quarter-finals at Roland
Garros was Franco Davin nine years ago, and the last to win the
tournament was Guillermo Vilas in 1977.
</P>
<P>
Squillari has never previously been beyond the second round in
a Grand Slam tournament.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
