<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK's Billiton Invests in China's Largest Zinc Mine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Billiton Corp. today
signed an agreement with the Yunnan Metallurgy Group for
developing the Lanping Zinc Mine, known as China's largest zinc
reserve.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will invest 500 million U.S. dollars to set up a
joint venture to manage the exploration, with the British partner
holding 65 percent of the stakes.
</P>
<P>
The new company, Huaying Zinc Co., will have a production
capacity of 200,000 tons of zinc in two to four years. By then,
the company is expected to have a high investment return rate of
over 12.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Lanping in northwest of Yunnan Province, southwest China, has
approved 10.5 million tons of zinc reserve and 2.26 million tons
of lead reserve.
</P>
<P>
Li Jiating, governor of Yunnan, and Brian Gilbertson, general
manager of Billiton, attended today's signing ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
