<HEADLINE> Smuggling of Cigarettes Cracked Down in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese customs today uncovered a
case of cigarette smuggling in southeast China, two Taiwan fishing
boats and seven suspects were detained.
</P>
<P>
The customs officials in the coastal city of Wenzhou in
Zhejiang Province, discovered 35 million cigarettes of 555, Hilton
and other brands in the hidden cabins of the two disguised Taiwan
boats.
</P>
<P>
The investigation of the case is underway.
</P>
<P>
The Wenzhou customs discovered cigarettes worth 16 million yuan
(1.9 million U.S. dollars) in another two Taiwan boats just two
days ago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
