<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fuzhou Ends Campaign to Seek Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A month-long campaign to seek
overseas investment concluded in here today, with the signing of
443 contracts which involved two billion U.S. dollars of overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
The biannual event this year featured the theme of exchanges
between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits, and science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 Chinese and overseas businessmen, including 52
of the top 500 multinational companies and diplomats of 26
countries to China, were in attendance. In addition, 82 Chinese
cities sent delegations.
</P>
<P>
Of the total contracts signed, 191 involved science and
technology, accounting for 43 percent of the total. The number of
Taiwan-funded projects stood at 102, or 23 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 seminars on various subjects of trade development
were held during the event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
