<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Declaration Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Pacific Regional Forum
on Urban Information approved the Shanghai Declaration today,
stressing promotion of mutual understanding and cooperation and a
narrowed gap in spread of information among countries in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The declaration says that economic globalization and
information exchange is the general trend of the social
development. Information trade is becoming the power behind all
fields including trade, investment, technical transfer.
</P>
<P>
The high-level forum cooperation committee for urban
information in Asian and Pacific regions will be set up based on
the principles of independence, equal opportunity and mutual
benefit.
</P>
<P>
An urban information appraisal system will also be built to
regularly compare the superiority and defects of cities in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The declaration states that the forum will be held annually.
</P>
<P>
Some 650 delegates attended the forum, including officials from
United Nations organizations, mayors of more than 40 cities from
the Asia-Pacific region, as well as a group of Chinese and
overseas specialists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
