<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High Temperatures Linger in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 6 (Xinhua) -- High temperatures will continue
to dominate south China's Guangdong Province for the next three
days, the Guangzhou municipal observatory reported today.
</P>
<P>
The hot weather has continued for a week. The maximum
temperature of many areas in the province yesterday hovered at
over 37 degrees Celsius, the highest on record for this day in 50
years. The temperature in Jieyang City even shot up to 39 degrees
Celsius.
</P>
<P>
A system of storms is approaching the province from the north
and starting to bring drizzle to the northern and eastern parts of
the province. But it is unlikely to expel the heat, according to
the weather forecast.
</P>
<P>
Most of the province will continue to be gripped by the 35-37
degree temperatures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
