<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of today's
diplomatic news released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
China Keen to Promote Relations with Myanmar
</P>
<P>
The further promotion of good-neighborly and cooperative
relations between China and Myanmar is an important part of China'
s diplomacy concerning its surrounding areas, Chinese Vice-
President Hu Jintao said here today.
</P>
<P>
During talks with Maung Aye, vice-chairman of the State Peace
and Development Council of Myanmar, Hu said that Sino-Myanmese
friendship and cooperation has been developing steadily over the
past decades despite the great changes that have taken place in
the international arena.
</P>
<P>
China, Myanmar Issue Joint Statement
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and visiting Myanmar
Foreign Minister U Win Aung signed here today on behalf of their
respective governments a joint statement on the framework of
future bilateral relations and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China Supports CTBT Early Entry into Force
</P>
<P>
China firmly supports the purposes and objectives of the
Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty (CTBT) and its early entry
into force and is ready to make its due contribution to it.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has submitted the treaty to the National
People's Congress for review and approval, Vice Foreign Minister
Wang Guangya said here today.
</P>
<P>
Viet Nam Confers Friendship Medals on Chinese FM, Diplomats
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese ambassador to China, Bui Hong Phuc, on behalf of
Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong, conferred friendship medals
on Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Assistant Foreign
Minister Wang Yi, here today, acknowledging their contribution to
promoting relations between the two countries and friendship
between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Botswana President to Visit China
</P>
<P>
President Festus Mogae of the Republic of Botswana will pay a
state visit to China from June 12 to 17 at the invitation of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Zhang
Qiyue announced here today.
</P>
<P>
NPC Chairman to Visit Six European and Asian Countries
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC) of China, will pay an official goodwill
visit to Yugoslavia, Slovenia, Croatia, Slovakia, Azerbaijan and
Ukraine from June 11 to 26, Foreign Ministry Spokeswoman Zhang
Qiyue also announced today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
