<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Children Have Huge Savings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey conducted in China'
s nine big cities shows that children between six and fifteen have
accumulated about 5.6 billion yuan (675 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The survey reveals that 87 percent of the 450 million children
in these cities including Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou have
their own "little banks."
</P>
<P>
On average, these children receive 60 yuan (about 7.2 U.S.
dollars) each month from their parents or relatives and 730 yuan (
88 U.S. dollars) on Chinese New Year.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, about two thirds of the children are
allowed to have free access to their savings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
