<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Red Cross Accepts Donation from US Pharmaceutical Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Red Cross Society today
accepted 600,000 yuan (72,289 U.S.dollars) worth of medical
supplies today from Pharmacia &AMP; Upjohn, a U.S.-based
pharmaceutical corporation, for a program to help 300 elderly
people regain their eyesight.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xizeng, vice chairman of the Beijing Red Cross Society,
said at today's donation ceremony that this gift has given a
tremendous boost to the ongoing "999 Sight Recovery Project" which
was initiated by the BRCS in February 1999 to help poverty-
stricken cataract sufferers regain their eyesight.
</P>
<P>
Over 50 percent of the world's blindness is caused by cataracts.
In China, about 400,000 people lose their sight due to cataracts
each year.
</P>
<P>
To date, the "999 Sight Recovery Project" has received 330,000
yuan (about 40,000 U.S.dollars) in contributions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
