<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Picture Album of CAE Academicians Published in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A photo album featuring scholars of
the Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE) was published in Beijing
today.
</P>
<P>
The two-volume album includes pictures, a brief biography and
short writings of 332 scholars who were elected from 1994 to 1996.
The set also records the achievements of engineering science and
technology in the country.
</P>
<P>
"The book will help encourage young and middle-aged scientists
to make more contributions to the country and attract more
youngsters to devote themselves to science and technology," said
Song Jian, president of the CAE and vice-president of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference today.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the third volume of Frontiers of
Science and Technology, which introduces the latest scientific
development in China, was also published today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
