<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton, Arafat to Meet in Washington in Mid-June: Albright </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will meet
with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on June 14 in the White
House,visiting U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright announced
Tuesday. Albright made the announcement at a press conference
after two-hour talks in the West Bank city of Ramallah with Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Israeli and Palestinian negotiators will resume their final-
status talks early next week in Washington, said Albright.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived in the Middle East region from Moscow Monday in
an effort to bridge the gaps between Israel and the Palestinians in
reaching a framework agreement on final-status issues.
</P>
<P>
She held talks with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak in
Jerusalem Monday and is scheduled to meet him again later Tuesday.
She will also meet Israeli President Ezer Weizman and her Israeli
counterpart David Levy during her return visit to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
She is due to arrive in Egypt Wednesday morning for discussions
with President Hosni Mubarak and Syrian Foreign Minister Faruk
Shareh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
