<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Delegation in Riyadh to Coordinate Positions on Maritime Border Dispute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Kuwaiti
delegation arrived in the Saudi capital of Riyadh on Tuesday to
coordinate their
positions on a long-standing maritime border dispute among Kuwait,
Saudi Arabia and Iran.
</P>
<P>
The two sides, led by Kuwaiti Oil Minister Sheikh al-Sabah and
Saudi Minister of Petroleum and Mineral Resources Ali al-N'aimi
respectively, will try to reach an agreement on the demarcation of
the borders on the Al-Dorra continental shelf in northern Gulf,
said reports reaching here from Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
The three Gulf states have been negotiating for years to try to
work out a demarcation scheme for the gas-rich continental shelf.
But no solution has been found so far.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Iran started drilling for gas in the disputed
area, triggering concern and protests from Kuwait and Saudi Arabia.
But Iran announced on May 13 the "halt of the operations".
</P>
<P>
Tehran has also reportedly expressed its readiness to open talks
with Kuwait and Saudi Arabia to reach an understanding on this
territorial dispute.
</P>
<P>
As the Kuwaiti-Saudi meeting comes ahead of the proposed
Kuwaiti-Saudi-Iranian meeting, likely to be held later in June, the
two Arab neighbors are expected to coordinate their positions on
the thorny border dispute.
</P>
<P>
The Saudis and Kuwaitis are also likely to discuss the date and
venue for the tripartite meeting, said Kuwaiti newspapers on
Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
