<HEADLINE> Share Prices Gain on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 19.29 points to
close at 2,001.72 points, back to the level above the 2,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 436.13 million shares worth 738.
81 million Singapore dollars (428.97 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outpaced losers by 195 to 127 with 220 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block was the 28.09 million parcel by Media-Rad
which was transacted at 0.49 Singapore dollars per share. It was
followed by Trek which had 22.51 million units done. SPHAsiaOne
was the next with 20.82 million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Chartered, Creative 50 and SIA led ascent of the day as they
picked up 70 cents each to close at 15.20, 47.60 and 17.50
Singapore dollars, respectively. SIA 200 gained 60 cents to finish
at 17.40 Singapore dollars. DBS climbed by 50 cents to end at 21.
60 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture led losers of the day incurring a loss of 50 cents to
close at 20.00 Singapore dollars. Thai Pr sank 46 cents to finish
at 3.54 U.S. dollars. StarCru retreated 25 cents to end at 6.50 U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers attributed Tuesday's higher close to selected buying.
</P>
<P>
They said that Asian stock markets were mixed, reflecting the
lackluster trend on Wall Street overnight, while holidays in Hong
Kong, Taiwan, and South Korea added to the lull. 
</P>
