<HEADLINE> EU Increases Food Aid to Eritrea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said
Tuesday it would provide an additional 20,000 tons of cereals to
Eritrea to assist the victims of war and drought.
</P>
<P>
The commission said the aid would also cover Eritrean refugees
currently residing in neighboring Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The commission decided on May 23 to provide Eritrea with 20,000
tons of cereals following the deteriorating humanitarian situation
in the African country.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's allocation of cereals will bring the total amount of
cereals committed by the European Union to Eritrea for delivery
this year to 65,400 tons.
</P>
<P>
After studying the situation in Eritrea, the European Community
Humanitarian Office has found it necessary to provide more urgent
food aid for the country.
</P>
<P>
The commission also said it was alarmed at the humanitarian
disaster caused by the conflict between Eritrea and Ethiopia.
</P>
