<HEADLINE> France to Study Russian Proposal for Anti-Missile System in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- France said Tuesday it will study the
proposal by Russian President Vladimir Putin for building an anti-
missile system in Europe in collaboration with NATO and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
"We will study it in details, in all its dimensions. We should
see what are the implications of the proposal of Mr. Putin," said
French Foreign Ministry spokesman Francois Rivasseau.
</P>
<P>
He said that France and Russia have so far shared the same
reservation about the U.S. plan to build a National Missile
Defense System.
</P>
<P>
France also opposes the U.S. intention to revise the Anti-
Ballistic Missile (ABM) treaty signed with the former Soviet Union
in 1972, as it could trigger a new global strategic arms race.
</P>
<P>
Putin said in Rome Monday that he was considering the creation
of an anti-missile defense system for Europe with the
participation of Europe, NATO and the United States.
</P>
<P>
He made the suggestion one day after a summit meeting with U.S.
President Bill Clinton in Moscow. 
</P>
