<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Science Against Superstition" Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A book titled Science Against
Superstition has been published by a local publishing house to
promote belief in fact over fiction.
</P>
<P>
The book was jointly compiled by the Organization Department of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, the
Department of Publicity of the CPC Central Committee and the China
Association for Science and Technology.
</P>
<P>
It contains Marxism's fundamental ideas on science and the CPC'
s practice on science-oriented belief.
</P>
<P>
The book analyzes why superstitions such as the officially-
banned cult Falun Gong have become so widespread. It also
clarifies definitions of religion and superstition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
