<HEADLINE> Four Zambian PeaceKeepers Missing in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Four Zambian peacekeeping soldiers
captured last month by Sierra Leonean rebels were missing, Zambian
Defence Minister Chitalu Sampa said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said at a news briefing that of all the 776 soldiers Zambia
sent to the western African country as part of U.N. peacekeeping
forces, 432 were captured by the rebel Revolutionary United Front
(RUF) and 428 were set free later with the remaining four
missing.
</P>
<P>
Concerted efforts are being made to establish the whereabouts
of the missing soldiers, said Sampa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
