<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Tourism Festival Attracts Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The scenic Three Gorges in
southwest China's Chongqing Municipality is expected to see a
surge in tourists with the opening of the Three Gorges Tourism
Festival today.
</P>
<P>
It's the fifth year for the annual tourism festival, but
sponsors said this year's event may attract more attention because
of the central government-initiated strategy of developing the
west.
</P>
<P>
Extending more than 500 kilometers, the Three Gorges is well-
known for its beautiful scenery and abundant cultural relics on
both banks of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The site became the hottest tourist destination in 1997 after
the Chinese government announced its plan to build the biggest
hydropower station on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The tourism festival of 2000 is a major component of the
municipality's ambitious program to develop the west, which is
expected to create a bridge between overseas tourists and
investors and the vast western areas in China, said Bao Xuding,
mayor of Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 guests have been invited to the 15-day tourism
festival, during which an international symposium will also be
held to attract more overseas investment to facilitate the western
expansion program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
