<HEADLINE> Oculists Offer Free Consultation on China's Healthy Eye Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Many opthamologists from Tongren
Hospital in Beijing, which is renowned for its advanced eye care
treatment, took to the street to give people basic information on
caring for their eyes to mark today's National Healthy Eye Day.
</P>
<P>
The year's Eye Day focused on the restoration of eyesight for
cataract patients. Some eye doctors at the hospital gave several
impoverished cataract patients living on the outskirts of Beijing
free cataract operations.
</P>
<P>
Cataracts are the leading eye problem in both developed and
developing countries. Some half of the 10 million eye disease
patients in China are cataract sufferers.
</P>
<P>
Surgery is considered to be the only effective way for cataract
patients to regain eyesight. Over 10,000 cataract operations are
done in Beijing every year.
</P>
<P>
Among those who have received the operation in Tongren Hospital,
the eldest is 106 years old and the youngest, two months old.
</P>
