<HEADLINE> Southeast University Celebrates 98th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Southeast China University held a
ceremony here today to celebrate its 98th founding anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Present at the occasion were Weiyu, vice-minister of education,
Cai Qinghua, vice-minister of Railways, Zhang Chunxian, vice-
minister of communications and noted educators and scholars from
Britain and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The university's chairman of the board was founded this morning.
Gu Guanqun, a scholar with the Chinese Academy of Engineering and
president of Southeast China University, was selected president of
the board.
</P>
