<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ten Million Afflicted with Diabetes in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 6 (Xinhua) -- More than ten million people in
Pakistan are afflicted with diabetes and their number is rising at
an alarming rate, health experts said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to experts from Pakistan Diabetic Association, at
present Pakistan is ranked at number 15 in the world in the number
of diabetics, but the increasing patients will put the country at
number five in the next 20 years if proper attention is not given
to prevent this deadly disease.
</P>
<P>
Diabetes develops when the pancreas does not produce enough
insulin or when the body cannot use the insulin properly. This
leads to a buildup of glucose in the blood which can seriously
damage various body organs, especially the blood vessels and
nerves.
</P>
<P>
The experts warned that while education could help in complete
prevention of 80 per cent diabetic complications,public awareness
about the disease is almost negligible in Pakistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
