<HEADLINE> Jobless Rates Slightly Down in Euro Zone, EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate fell
slightly last March in both the euro zone and the European Union (
EU), Eurostat said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical office of the European
community said that the jobless rate for the 11-nation euro zone
went down to 9.2 percent in March from 9.3 percent in the previous
month while the jobless rate for the 15-nation EU dropped from 8.6
percent to 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
In April last year, the unemployment rate for the euro zone was
10.1 percent and that for the EU was 9.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the last 12 months, the biggest drop in unemployment was
witnessed in Ireland where the jobless rate dropped from 5.9
percent to 4.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the EU member states, the lowest jobless rate was still
registered in Luxembourg with 2.2 percent, and Spain still posted
the highest unemployment rate at 14.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat estimated that 12 million men and women of the work-
force were jobless in the euro zone while 14.6 million people were
unemployed in the EU in April this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
