<HEADLINE> Trains to Run Faster on East China Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 6 (Xinhua) --The train speed on the railway line
between Huangshan, a tourism destination in Anhui Province, and
this capital of Jiangsu Province, will be increased to 80 km per
hour from the present 50 km per hour as of October 1.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Ministry of Railways today conducted a
successful experiment on the speed increase on the railway line.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed to raise the speed of trains between the
famous Huangshan Mountain and Nanjing to meet the needs of tourist
development and sharpen the competitive edge of railways, said a
local transportation official.
</P>
<P>
Every year, the site receives an average of four million
visitors and only 10 percent of them go by trains. The speed of
trains on the railway is slow at present since it zigzags across
the mountainous area.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, beginning October 1, it will take
passenger trains only five hours, about two and half hours less
than now, to travel from Nanjing to Huangshan. 
</P>
