<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics show that the
total number of Jinsui Card, the banking card issued by the
Agricultural Bank of China (ABC), has exceeded 30 million, with
card deposits surpassing 40 billion yuan (about 5.13 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ABC said that since the bank opened banking
card business in 1991, it has maintained a healthy growth momentum,
with the number of card issued, the outstanding card deposits and
total card consumption value ranking high on the list of the
country's major commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
He said that the ABC has basically established a nationwide
network for banking card business that is supported by new and
high technologies, connecting more than 300 cities, 86,000
commercial clients and over 42,000 banking card business outlets,
as well as 53,000 POSs and 3,600 ATMs.
</P>
<P>
He said that presently the ABC is making further efforts to
improve the environment for card business development, including
the upgrading of the existing nationwide network and the
construction of citywide networks. 
