<HEADLINE> Number of Chinese Cybersurfers Exceeds 10 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of Chinese Internet
surfers has exceeded 10 million, statistics provided by the China
Internet Network Information Center (CINIC) show.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts say that this marks a milestone in China's
history of Internet development.
</P>
<P>
Internet was available in China in 1994. Since then, the number
of Chinese cybersurfers has kept increasing. By October of 1997,
the number of Internet users reached 620,000, and by the end of
1999, the number topped 8.9 million.
</P>
<P>
CINIC, who is in charge of disclosing information on China's
Internet development, began issuing the numbers of net users and
PCs twice a year since November of 1997.
</P>
<P>
China is expected to become one of the world's largest Internet
markets.  
</P>
