<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday on continued selective
selling activity on index-linked counters.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100 quality stocks Composite Index lost 9.60
points to 871.79, the all-share Emas Index fell 2.58 points to 219.
38, the Industrial Index slipped 32.37 points to 1,529.25 and the
Second Board Index dropped 3.56 points to 228.77.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 583 to 104 while 135 counters were
unchanged and 157 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover decreased to 122.705 million shares valued
at 421.775 million ringgit (110.993 million U.S. dollars) from 142.
540 million shares valued at 719.16 million ringgit (189.252
million U.S. dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
