<HEADLINE> Another Earthquake Hits Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.0 on the
Richter Scale hit Sukabumi regency, Indonesia's West Java province
on Tuesday, Antara News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
An officials of the National Earthquake Center said that the
first tremors took place at about 00:43 a.m. local time (1743 GMT
Monday) and lasted for several seconds.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported following the quake which was
located 18 kilometers below the earth's surface in the Indian
Ocean.
</P>
<P>
But the report said that the Tuesday's tremor was also felt in
Bandung, capital of West Java province and Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the death toll in a powerful earthquake on Sunday
hit Bengkulu province on Sumatra island has risen to 103 and
leaving more than 500 others injured. 
</P>
