<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Pays Large Money Bunuses for Sydney Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ASTANA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan will offer 100,000 U.S.
dollars to their gold medal winners at this year's Sydney Olympic
Games, according to reports on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Our government will pay $100,000, $50,000 and $30,000
respectively to each athlete, who wins gold, silver and bronze
medals -- the same amount we paid our winners in Atlanta four
years ago," chairman of the Kazakh State Sports Committee Daulet
Turlykhanov was quoted by Reuters as saying.
</P>
<P>
"Furthermore, for the first time we also decided to pay
coaches whose athletes win Olympic titles at least $50,000,"
Turlykhanov continued.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan won 11 medals, three of them gold, at the 1996
Atlanta Olympics and want at least to match that showing in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan's best medal hopes lie in boxing and Greco-Roman
and freestyle wrestling. 
</P>
