<HEADLINE> CPPCC Meeting in Memory of Religious Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A group of ethnic and religious
members of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) gathered here today in memory of Zhao Puchu, an
outstanding religious leader who passed away recently.
</P>
<P>
Ngapoi Ngawang Jigme, a Vice-Chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee, called on the ethnic and religious circles to learn
from the patriotic religious leader and make new contributions to
the socialist cause with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
As a patriotic religious leader, Zhao had actively promoted
Buddhism, led the Buddhist believers to love the country and the
religion and made the religion accustomed to the socialist society.
</P>
<P>
Zhao had also supported the development of Tibetan Buddhism and
opposed the various schemes by overseas splittists, Ngapoi Ngawang
Jigme said.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Zheng Wantong, Secretary-
General of the CPPCC National Committee, and Zhao's wife Chen
Bangzhi. 
</P>
