<HEADLINE> Philippine Stocks Continue to Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Manila stocks continued to recover
Tuesday boosted by news the continued appreciation of the
Philippine peso may promote the Central Bank of the Philippines to
cut interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, added 9.73
points to close at 1,562.38. The broader all-share index was also
up by 7.85 points to 653.8.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 2.2 billion shares worth some 31 million U.S.
dollars on Tuesday against Monday's 2.5 billion shares worth some
27 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Traders said investors positioned in some blue chips and
secondary stocks amid better market sentiment but said trading
volume remained thin.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday's trading, gainers swamped losers, 63 to 43, while
33 issues closed unchanged. 
</P>
