<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Communications Event Opens in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 6 (Xinhua) -- CommunicAsia2000, regarded as the
top communications trade event in Asia, opened Tuesday here to
embrace more then 2,000 companies from 56 countries and regions,
the majority of whom are the world's key telecoms and IT players.
</P>
<P>
Making the largest presence at the event are famous brand names
like Lucent, Nortel Networks, Nokia, Ericsson, Motorola,
SunMicrosystems, Samsung, Siemens, Huawei and many others of a
similar league.
</P>
<P>
Group pavilions include Singapore, Canada, Finland, Germany,
Ireland, New Zealand, Spain, Switzerland, the United States, China,
Thailand and the South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Tan, managing director of organizer Singapore
Exhibition Services said the show size has grown by a significant
48 percent over its last show in 1999.
</P>
<P>
"The speed at which this industry moves is phenomenal and we
constantly find ourselves re-engineering the event to ensure we
are in tune with the industry," Tan said.
</P>
<P>
CommunicAsia2000 features seven theme pavilions -- eBiz2000,
MobileCommAsia200, NetworkAsia2000, BroadcastAsia2000,
Professional Audio Technology2000, CableSatellite2000 and
ComGraphics and Animation2000.
</P>
<P>
A new feature at this event is eBiz2000, a specialized showcase
on electronic commerce, internet business applications and
solutions. The e-Biz Feature Area houses internet companies and
banks and securities companies which have gone the e-commerce way.
</P>
<P>
Bluetooth, a newly-born technological innovation and a wireless
technology that can interconnect diverse mobile electronic devices,
will show its cutting-edge prowess with the display of many new
Bluetooth-enabled products.
</P>
<P>
Another area of focus at CommunicAsia2000, is Network Security,
a topical issue which forms the theme for the info-security
pavilion.
</P>
<P>
Since its first exhibition held in 1979, CommunicAsia has grown
to become Asia's largest telecoms IT event.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day exhibition period this year,
CommunicAsia2000 is expected to attract more than 18,000
exhibitors and 35,000 trade visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
