<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya to Face Dry Weather in Next Four Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 6 (Xinhua) -- For the next four months,
three-quarters of Kenya will remain dry as the expected rains will
not alleviate the current drought, local meteorologists have
warned.
</P>
<P>
The Kenya Meteorological Department predicted that water and
power problems will persist for the next four months as of June,
Daily Nation newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The only season that would turn around the sorry situation is
the October-December rains," said Evans Mukolwe, head of the
meteorological department.
</P>
<P>
Mukolwe said in the next months, only the Lake Victoria basin,
the western highlands and the southern coastal region will receive
significant rainfall, while other parts of the country would
experience below-normal rainfall.  !!
</P>
<P>
Mukolwe also mentioned that apart from southern Tanzania, other
parts of East Africa are experiencing severe drought.
</P>
<P>
The department said Kenya is facing one of the longest and
severest droughts since 1984, and a number of locations in the
country recorded the lowest rainfall totals during this year's
long rains (March to May) in the past 40 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
