<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Launches New Sedan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen Corp.
announced here today the launching of the company's Passat Sedan
on the Chinese market at the Auto China 2000 Show.
</P>
<P>
The new sedan is the third generation of sedan produced by the
Shanghai Volkswagen Corp. after the Santana and the Santana 2000.
</P>
<P>
The new design was based on the prototype Passat sedan of the
Germany-based Volkswagenwerk, and certain modifications were made
to cater to the specific needs of Chinese consumers.
</P>
<P>
An economic type of Shanghai Passat, with 52.82 percent of
parts localization, is priced at 245,000 yuan, while a luxury type,
with 45.38 percent of localization, coasts 289,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The new sedan has so far passed an evaluation conducted jointly
by officials and experts from numerous State government
departments. 
