<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ABM Treaty Must Be Maintained, FM Spokeswoman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua)-- China supports Russia's position to
maintain the integrity and validity of the Anti-Ballistic Missile
(ABM) treaty, said Zhang Qiyue, Chinese foreign ministry
spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
She made the remarks here today at a regular press conference
in response to a relevant question.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the adherence to the ABM treaty is conducive
to the maintenance of international strategic balance and
stability, and conforms to the common interests of all countries.
</P>
<P>
She said that plans to set up missile defense systems and to
revise or withdraw the ABM treaty will not only affect the process
and shake the basis of nuclear disarmament, but also bring about a
new arms race, including an arms race in the outer space.
</P>
<P>
Such plans will do no good to any country in the world, Zhang
stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
