<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Lanzhou, Xining and Yinchuan in
northwestern China suffered slight air pollution today, while
Beijing, Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan, Hohhot, Nantong and Yantai had
extremely slight air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center,
said that Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou,
Hangzhou, Guangzhou, Wuhan and 17 other cities enjoyed fairly good
air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Fuzhou, Xiamen, Shenzhen, Zhuhai,
Haikou, Kunming and Lhasa, all in the south and the southwest, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Taiyuan, Beijing, Tianjin, Xi'an, Shanghai and 27 other cities
listed absorbable suspended particles as the major pollutants,
while sulfur dioxide was the major pollutant in Guiyang, Nanning
and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 key coastal cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
