<HEADLINE> Landmines Cleared Away in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 6 (Xinhua) -- China has succeeded in clearing
away the landmines within its territory after two campaigns of
minesweeping, the Liberation Army Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Since the end of the campaigns half a year ago, no human and
animal death or injury has been reported from the south and
southwest border areas, where a lot of mines and other explosives
had been left due to past border clashes.
</P>
<P>
The two campaigns have ridded the areas of 1.88 million
landmines and 320,000 pieces of other explosives. A total of 60,
000 hectares of farming land and forests have been reclaimed in
the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and Yunnan Province, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
The successful minesweeping has resulted in the reopening of
290 border passages and ports, bringing prosperity to the border
areas.
</P>
<P>
The minesweeping efforts by the Chinese military have also won
praises from visiting officials of the United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
