<HEADLINE> Pakistan Outplays Sri Lanka in Asia Cup Cricket </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Tuesday recorded a morale-
boosting seven-wicket win over defending champion Sri Lanka Monday
at the Bangabandhu National Stadium ahead of Wednesday's final of
the seventh Asia Cup Cricket.
</P>
<P>
The last league match of the four-team meet was rather dull,
unlike the other blood-and-thunder clashes featuring tons of runs,
according to The Independent newspaper report on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of the match, a dress rehearsal of tomorrow's final,
would certainly put Pakistan in a better frame of mind ahead of
the islanders who conceded their first defeat in the four-nation
meet after two successive wins over Bangladesh and India.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding performance of Yousuf Youhana of Pakistan in
this match earned him the man-of-the-match for the second
successive game.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, the Asian Cricket Foundation (ACF)
was launched Monday in Dhaka with pledges to combat financial
crimes from the world of cricket and ensure welfare of regional
cricketers.
</P>
<P>
In its first formal meeting, the foundation, which will work
under the guidance of Asian Cricket Council (ACC), formed an anti-
corruption committee that would be on the alert for financial
crimes and incidents of gross irregularities in the sporting
discipline.
</P>
<P>
The ACF will start functioning after getting approval from the
ACC which is scheduled to meet in London later this month during
the International Cricket Council meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
