<HEADLINE> 5.9-Magnitude Earthquake Jolts North Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.9-degree on
the Richter scale hit Turkey's Cankiri Province, some 100
kilometers north of the capital city Ankara, early Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which took place at 5:40 a.m. local time (0240 GMT),
killed at least two people and was strongly felt in Ankara.
</P>
<P>
According to a report released by the Prime Ministry's crisis-
controlling center, the epicenter was located in Cerkes county.
</P>
<P>
The tremor was one of the largest quakes that followed last
year's two major earthquakes, one being 7.4-magnitude in Marmara
region in western Turkey and another 7.2-magnitude in Bolu
Province, which is adjacent to Cankiri Province. 
