<HEADLINE> Australian PM: Solomons Has to Find Its Own Solution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Australia made a deliberate
decision to refuse the Solomon Islands prime minister's urgent
plea for Australian police to avert a coup, Prime Minister John
Howard said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Howard told backbenchers at a joint party room meeting that
Australian Federal Police could have been caught up in the
domestic conflict which resulted in the Solomon Islands' Prime
Minister Bartholomew Ulufa'alu being seized by rebels.
</P>
<P>
