<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Lifts Censorship On Foreign Media </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government lifted
the military censorship on the foreign media based in the country
from Tuesday, according to a news release issued by the government
information Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The censorship on the foreign media was imposed under the
Regulations promulgated under the Public Security Act on May 3
after the country was placed on a war footing by the Sri Lankan
president.
</P>
<P>
The Regulations were issued followed military reversals
suffered by government forces in the northern Jaffna peninsula in
Tamil rebels' ferocious attacks.
</P>
<P>
In lifting the censorship, the release said the foreign media
would act with a sense of responsibility complying with the
Regulations without any prejudice to the national interest of the
country. 
</P>
