in this year's first quarter, showing a vigorous recovery
following a severe fall in 1999, Venezuela's ambassador Fernando
Gerbassi said Monday. (Colombia-Venezuela-Trade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian Agriculture Minister Marcus Vicinius
Pratini de Moraes Monday called for more investment in agriculture
in order to raise this sector's competitivity in the market.
</P>
<P>
With the use of barely 127 million hectares of delimited land,
Brazil will be able to triple its current production of grain up
to 250 million tons a year, together with 90 million tons of
fruits and 11 million tons of meat, said the minister.  (Brazil-
Agriculture)
</P>
