- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syria and Qatar have agreed to cut down tariffs on
imported goods on a reciprocal basis by up to 70 percent by 2002
and to tax free a year later, Syrian Arab News Agency reported
Monday. (Syria-Qatar-Communique)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- Canada's net debt is predicted to drop to 568.8
billion Canadian dollars in 2000 (about 385.6 billion U.S. dollars)
, the country's Globe and Mail newspaper said Monday.  (Canada's
Debt)
</P>
