<HEADLINE> BIMST-EC Energy Meeting Held in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 6 (Xinhua) -- A meeting of the committee of
experts and officials relating to an energy sector cooperation
program of the BIMST-EC, a sub-regional economic grouping
comprising Bangladesh, India, Myanmar, Sri Lanka and Thailand, is
being held here to formulate a plan of action, the New Light of
Myanmar reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening session of the two-day meeting on Monday,
Myanmar Energy Minister Brigadier-General Lun Thi said the BIMST-
EC program is now in its third year of existence during which
sectors for cooperation had been identified.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of laying down action plans that
could be translated into strategies to be pursued and implemented
by all member countries.
</P>
<P>
The two projects for cooperation in the energy sector already
identified by the BIMST-EC are the natural gas resources and the
renewable energy sources, both of which are abundant in the region.
</P>
<P>
He called for intensive exploration and exploitation of the
resources as well as development of the related infrastructure and
long-term sustainable utilization of these resources.
</P>
<P>
The minister pledged Myanmar's support for all efforts of the
BIMST-EC to develop the region socially and economically.
</P>
<P>
The BIMST-EC was first formed by four countries -- Bangladesh,
India, Sri Lanka and Thailand -- in June 1997 and was later joined
by Myanmar in August that year.
</P>
<P>
In July 1999, Myanmar formed a national committee on
cooperation with BIMST-EC countries in the energy sector. 
</P>
