held on schedule, the official Daily News reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The new general elections are due by August 16 this year.
</P>
<P>
The president told the British Broadcasting Corporation's
Sinhala "Sandeshaya" program here on Monday that the present
parliament must be dissolved by the last week of August this year
and the new elections must be concluded within eight weeks
thereafter.
</P>
<P>
She said she would stick to the general elections timetable and
would not postpone the polls.
</P>
<P>
She told the BBC that as her government had ruled the country
respecting the Constitution and democracy, the general elections
will be held on time despite various obstacles.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga added that the censorship on the media imposed by
her on May 3 will be lifted. She expressed the hope that the local
press would act responsibly.
</P>
<P>
The censorship and other severe regulations were imposed under
the Public Security Act by the president after placing the country
on a war footing following government forces' reversals in the
Jaffna peninsula in their war against separatist Tamil rebels who
have been fighting for a separate Tamil state in the country's
north and east since 1983.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that government troops now have a clear strategy
to hold on to the peninsula. 
</P>
