<HEADLINE> Mine Blast Injures Two Kosovars in Albanian Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Two Kosovo citizens were injured on
Sunday by a mine explosion in the vicinity of the Qafe Prush
customs checkpoint, 120 meters from the border on the Albanian
side.
</P>
<P>
The two Kosovo citizens walked across a mine zone at about 15:
15 p.m. in the vicinity of Qafe Prush. Due to the mine blast one
of them lost his leg, while the other was badly wounded in the
face, a spokesman for the Has police commissariat said.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to the Gajkove hospital.
</P>
<P>
So far, eight persons have lost their lives, while 42 others
have been injured due to mine explosions along the 26-kilometer-
long borderline in the Has district.
</P>
