<HEADLINE> Sinn Fein Wins First Mayoral Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Sinn Fein, the political wing of the
Irish Republican Army (IRA), won the office of mayor of Northern
Ireland's second largest city of Londonderry on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Cathal Crumley, 41, who served four years in prison after being
convicted of IRA membership, won Londonderry's mayoral election to
become the party's first mayor in 80 years. He received backing
from 21 of the city council's 30 members.
</P>
<P>
The election of Crumley followed the narrow defeat of the
party's nominee for Belfast's mayoral chain last week.
</P>
<P>
Londonderry has majority Roman Catholic population. 
