<HEADLINE> Albanian Police Destroy Large Amount of Cannabis Plants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 5 (Xinhua) -- Albanian police destroyed more than
50,000 cannabis plants and summoned 40 cultivators in May,
according to the Albanian Ministry of Public Order on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The greatest amount of cannabis plants was destroyed in
Llakatund, Vlore, Borishove, Fier and several other districts in
southern Albania, it said.
</P>
<P>
Cultivation of cannabis in Albania began in 1992 when villagers
started growing cannabis in their plots near the border with
Greece and Italy.
</P>
<P>
About 80 tons of unprocessed cannabis was smuggled into Greece
and Italy from Albania between 1992-1996, according to police
statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
