<HEADLINE> Montoya Wins International CART Race in Wisconsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 5 (Xinhua) -- The defending CART series
champion Juan Montoya of Colombia Monday defeated his rivals to
win the rain-postponed Miller Lite 225 CART FedEx Championship
Series race at the Milwaukee Mile, Wisconsin.
</P>
<P>
Montoya started from the pole in the race delayed one day and
led all but 42 of the 225 laps on the 1.660-kilometer oval, giving
Toyota's Champ car engine its first victory in five years and 78
CART races.
</P>
<P>
Although he led 40 percent of the laps in the first five CART
events this season, Montoya had not finished better than fourth
this year until taking the race at Indy.
</P>
<P>
Montoya became the sixth different winner in CART this season
and leaped from 10th in the points into a tie for fourth with
American Michael Andretti, Monday's runner-up.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Paul Tracy, the defending race winner, finished a
disappointing 15th in the 23-car field, but held on to the series
lead with 59 points. Roberto Moreno finished fifth and moved into
second, seven points behind Tracy and four ahead of Jimmy Vasser.
Montoya and Andretti both have 44 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
