<HEADLINE> Russia to Raise Annual Oil Production to 340 Million Tons by 2015 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russia will increase annual oil
production to 340 million tons by 2015, Russian Deputy Fuel and
Energy Minister Valery Garipov told journalists Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Russia's oil production will grow 7 million tons to 310-312
million tons in 2000, and within 15 years 70 percent of national
oil will be produced in Western Siberia, compared to the current
68 percent, Garipov announced at a national seminar on the
development of Russian oil deposits, in the city of Almetevsk.
</P>
<P>
The oil output will rise thanks to the development of new
deposits, the renewal of operations at idle wells and the
introduction of new production technology.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar, Tatarstan presidential aide Rinat
Muslimov predicted that the republic will provide the country with
over 27 million tons of oil this year.
</P>
<P>
According to Muslimov, about 23 million tons of this will be
produced by Tatarstan's largest oil enterprise Tatneft and over 4
million tons by 27 small oil companies in the republic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
