valuable back-up to the United Nations operation, including better
communications and military advice for its headquarters.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, Cook also revealed that he is to visit Sierra
Leone for a meeting on Thursday with President Ahmad Tejan Kabba
to discuss what else the United Kingdom could do to help.
</P>
<P>
He said Britain was the "lead nation" in training a new Sierra
Leone army.
</P>
<P>
