<HEADLINE> Moldovan Government Tries to Avoid New Rise in Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The Moldovan government decided
to issue for free 1,800 tons of wheat flour from the state reserve
to the country's largest bakery Franzeluta, in a bid to avoid a
new rise in prices, the Prime Minister Dumitru Braghis told a
press conference on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After the "bread crisis" is overcome definitively, Franzeluta
will have to return the flour, the Prime Minister stressed.
</P>
<P>
Braghis is confident that the prices of bakery products will
not grow more expensive in June as there is no reasons to raise
the prices again. According to him, the recent bread crisis had
been unleashed artificially by bakeries and certain business
people in order to push up the prices.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this week, the government will gather all main
bread producers to try and resolve the problem of price formation.
</P>
<P>
"We do not see any reasons for such a pushing up of prices till
the next harvest", stressed Braghis. 
