<HEADLINE> Mercosur to Arrive at a Single Currency: Brazilian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 6 (Xinhua)-- Southern Common Market (Mercosur)
will be able to adopt a single currency like European Union, in 15
years, said Tuesday Brazilian special representative for Mercosur
affairs, Ambassador Jose Botafogo Gonzalves.
</P>
<P>
The official said this hypothesis will be discussed again next
week in Buenos Aires, during a working meeting of representatives
of the four countries making up this block.
</P>
