Botafogo also spoke about Mercosur's opportunities of surviving
as healthy block, indicating the four partners must make internal
adjustments, to eliminate risks of going back to inflation while
reducing dependence on external capital.
</P>
<P>
As regards recent adjustments made by Argentina's government,
this ambassador said they must not have a negative effect but, on
the short term, there will be some negative as regards trade.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur is composed by Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay,
with Bolivia and Chile as associate members.  
