<P>
According to projections of this state organism, by year 2001,
the output will be 4.61 million metric tons, increasing by 1.3
percent which can be explained through "the absence of new big
copper projects".
</P>
<P>
When presenting "Year Book of Copper and Other Minerals 1990-
1999", COCHILCO said investing in the mining sector this year will
go up to 1.36 billion dollars, of which 700 million dollars will
come from foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
As regards foreign trade, he highlighted that copper refining
is the main export product, with 60 percent of dispatches.
Regarding destinations, he said that in this decade exports to
Europe doubled and those meant for Asia and America tripled.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
