<DOCNO> XIE20000606.0342 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moldovan Economy Is Growing this Year, Prime Minister Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The industrial output in Republic
Moldova has grown up by 35.8 percent from the beginning of this
year, compared with the same period last year, Prime Minister
Dumitru Braghis stated on Tuesday at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"In comparable prices, the growth figure in the national
economy as a whole was 3.9 percent", he said, adding "these are
very good indicators for Moldova which must be necessarily
consolidated".
</P>
<P>
Asked about external debt repaying, the Prime Minister stated
that heretofore his Cabinet has not been late with even a single
external payment. "This year, we cannot count on putting off our
due payments to international financial institutions", Braghis
added.
</P>
<P>
"There exist no real hope to expect this. The situation can
only be relieved by borrowing new credits for redeeming new ones",
said the Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
He told the media that the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
and the World Bank are ready to continue cooperation with Moldova.
Presently, the Government is drafting a new Memorandum of
cooperation with these institutions.
</P>
<P>
In July, an IMF mission is expected to arrive in Chisinau to
negotiate a new program -- to fight poverty. According to this
program, Moldova will be able to receive new IMF loans for longer
periods and at lower interest rates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
